# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# OpenTeddy Fleet — WORKER node .env
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# Copy this to EACH worker node's .env. Every worker uses this template, but
# two values differ per machine: OPENTEDDY_FLEET_NODE_ID and
# OPENTEDDY_FLEET_NODE_ROLE.
#
#   cp fleet/env.worker.example .env       # fresh install, OR
#   cat fleet/env.worker.example >> .env   # append to existing
#
# Then edit the two per-node values below + the central URL, and restart
# OpenTeddy. The worker auto-dials the central + waits for tasks.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Shared secret — MUST be IDENTICAL to the central's OPENTEDDY_FLEET_TOKEN.
# This is the same value you generated once with `openssl rand -hex 32` and
# pasted on the central. Copy that exact string here.
OPENTEDDY_FLEET_TOKEN=paste-the-same-long-random-secret-as-the-central

# Role for THIS node. Workers are "worker".
OPENTEDDY_FLEET_ROLE=worker

# WebSocket URL of the central orchestrator. Replace with the central's
# hostname or IP + its OPENTEDDY_FLEET_PORT. e.g.
#   ws://dgx-01.local:8770   or   ws://192.168.111.167:8770
OPENTEDDY_FLEET_CENTRAL=ws://CHANGE-ME-central-host:8770

# ── Per-node identity (CHANGE THESE on each worker) ──────────────────────────

# A human-meaningful id shown in the central's node list. Defaults to the
# machine hostname if unset — but set it explicitly so the fleet view is clear.
OPENTEDDY_FLEET_NODE_ID=dgx-02

# This node's functional role in the fleet — a free-form label the central
# will use to route tasks by responsibility (milestone 4). Examples:
#   finance / hr / sales / external-intel / secops / sys-health
OPENTEDDY_FLEET_NODE_ROLE=finance

# ── Proactive watcher (optional — the "raises a hand on its own" feature) ────
# When enabled, this node periodically self-checks its area of responsibility
# and pushes an ALERT to the central (→ console Alerts tab + Telegram) when it
# finds something worth a human's attention. OFF unless you set =1.
OPENTEDDY_FLEET_WATCH_ENABLED=0

# How often the watcher self-checks, in seconds. Default 900 (15 min) is a
# sane production cadence. Drop to 120 while testing so you see alerts fast;
# raise it if the check is expensive (big model / heavy data scan).
OPENTEDDY_FLEET_WATCH_INTERVAL=900

# Cooldown (seconds) before the SAME observation may alert again. Stops a
# genuine-but-persistent condition (disk 85%, a service down) re-firing every
# cycle — you get one ping, not a stream. Default 3600 (1h).
OPENTEDDY_FLEET_ALERT_COOLDOWN=3600

# IMPORTANT: if OPENTEDDY_FLEET_WATCH_PROMPT below is left UNSET, the watcher
# runs no checks and raises NO alerts — by design. A generic "is anything
# unusual?" prompt with no real data source makes a reasoning model invent
# warning/critical alerts every cycle. Define a concrete check below to
# activate alerting.

# What the watcher checks. THIS is the node-specific part — write a prompt
# describing what "abnormal" means for THIS node's data + tools. The watcher
# automatically appends a machine-readable ANOMALY/SEVERITY/CONFIDENCE block,
# so you only write the "what to look at" part. Leave unset to use a generic
# placeholder (which mostly reports "no anomaly" — fine for proving the
# pipeline, useless for real monitoring).
#
# Examples by role (uncomment + adapt ONE):
#
#   finance:
#     OPENTEDDY_FLEET_WATCH_PROMPT=檢查 /data/finance 最近一小時的交易紀錄，是否有異常大額付款、首次出現的收款方、或批次資料被竄改的跡象。
#
#   secops:
#     OPENTEDDY_FLEET_WATCH_PROMPT=檢查系統登入日誌（/var/log/auth.log）最近一小時是否有暴力登入嘗試、來自異常地理位置的成功登入、或權限提升行為。
#
#   sys-health:
#     OPENTEDDY_FLEET_WATCH_PROMPT=檢查本機磁碟用量、記憶體、關鍵服務（docker、ollama）是否正常運作，有任何接近滿載或已停止的就回報。
#
#   external-intel:
#     OPENTEDDY_FLEET_WATCH_PROMPT=用可用工具查最近一小時是否有與本公司/產業相關的重大新聞、資安通報或輿情變化。
#
# OPENTEDDY_FLEET_WATCH_PROMPT=（在這裡寫這台節點要檢查什麼）
